Azure subscription — Make sure that you have an active Azure subscription. Is it your first time ‘wandering around’ in Azure? Most of the time you can get a free starters account with free credits to spend that covers the scope of this tutorial!
GitHub repository — Make sure to clone the repository to your development machine.
Python — The Django application in the app directory is written with Python 3, follow this installation guide.
Docker — Download and install Docker according the official installation guide for your operating system.
Azure CLI — Make sure that the Azure Command Line Interface is integrated in your system’s command-line tool.
kubectl — We will set up the kubectl Kubernetes command-line client tool in step 3 and configure it for your AKS cluster.
Helm — Helm 3 is a Kubernetes package manager. We will install this tool in step 4.